What happened this “day” was thrilling. I felt my body… though it has long ceased to exist… embraced by an unprecedented sensation. For this reason, I’ve gone out of my way to write in my diary before this long “day” is over. Yes, I’m certain that this “day” will be incredibly long.

At this moment, what pains me the most is that I must write down the changes that occurred today chronologically. This is the bottom line, otherwise my writing will lack basic logic, which is a fault I’d never want to see in the future.

Two things happened in all. The first was that marvelous cataclysm. Of course, I knew a little more about it than the city representatives. After all, I do possess knowledge of the Honkai. And as a result, those two Vitas believed that I could help them and find a way to end the cataclysm. They’ve actually thrown themselves at my feet.

As for the second thing, it was wonderful, horrible, and truly unforgettable. When I saw that face again, what was the first thought that came to my mind? Surprise, naturally, no one would’ve thought that I’d meet a fellow countryperson on this distant planet; Fear, justifiably so, knowing that my predecessor, the former vessel of this spirit, was, by her hand… No, there was another emotion that far surpassed them both. Yes, it was joy. A joy based on reason.

For the last few “days”, my exploration of this new world has always been hindered by problems concerning the forbidden area. By trial and error, I can almost prove that the forbidden area is a space that cannot be stepped into. When I was at an impasse, however, a variable presented herself to me. She was brand-new, pure, extraordinarily powerful, and I know her inside out. If I lead her to the forbidden area and use her to open that tempting door for me… I will make discoveries and gains like never before.

Yes, this is enough. As for the rest of my personal feelings, I can leave them aside for now. Now, to facilitate this fascinating plan, I will head over to the audience seats tailored for me, and enjoy this one-sided, long-awaited reunion…
